description.0: Peter disposes of Spider-Clone's body, convinced that he is the true Spider-Man. At an engagement party for Ned Leeds and Betty Brant, Peter discovers the return of Shocker! And this time, the villain has left a calling card that all of NYC can't miss!
description.1: Thor, Moondragon and Immortus travel back to the year 1873 searching for their missing comrade!
description.2: Its fight or flight for the Star-Spangled Soldier, literally. Can Captain America manage to survive the slaughter in the sky?
description.15: Daredevil mistakes Torpedo for a villain, and he acts accordingly!
description.18: Captain Marvel is once again combined with Rick Jones! But if Mar-Vell messes up…Rick's life is the one on the line.
description.29: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 13: T'Challa is attacked and held captive by Killmonger's better half, Madam Slay!
description.32: Dr. Leonard Samson, PhD, is a victim in a gamma ray explosion. Introducing...Doc Samson!
description.33: Iron Man follows Firebrand into an Earth unlike our own and to survive, they may just have to fight side-by-side.
description.35: Odin believes himself to be the Egyptian god Atum-Re and he's looking to destroy Thor - not knowing that he's actually his own son!
description.36: Dracula's weakened state has left him unconscious! What can save him now from Dr. Sun and his mysterious acolyte, Juno?
description.37: While Johnny Storm is painting the town red on a date with Frankie Raye, New York City becomes the target of an attack from the Crusader. Will Johnny's date still be into him when she discovers his true identity as the Human Torch?
description.40: Following his battle with Jackal and a Spider-Clone, Spider-Man questions whether he is the real web-slinger or a clone injected with memories. Spidey seeks the help of Dr. Curt Connors, but before the results are revealed, Spencer Smythe arrives on the scene with new Spider-Slayer weaponry!
description.41: The Beast is attacked by a group of costumed criminals armed with high tech weapons!
description.42: The Falcon has a hit on him. Can the dynamic duo manage to defeat the murderous Stilt Man before he can complete his mission? Find out in the trial of the Falcon!
description.44: Torpedo's biggest threat in battle may not be Daredevil, but watching out for that WAL…too late.
description.54: The Dezlany Studio turns on Johnny Blaze and Stuntmaster when the crew falls under the possession of the Orb!
description.55: The Hulk has a Scottish adventure when he battles the fabled Loch Ness monster!
description.56: Doctor Kurarkill pulls the rug from underneath the Golden Avengers as he pins Quasar against Iron Man in a deadly match that will leave you speechless! Read to find out the outcome!
description.57: Have they finally located Odin at last? And what do the gods of Egypt have to do it?
description.58: The stage is set! Dracula stalks the streets of Boston, Frank Drake returns to the U.S., and Dr. Sun summons a new servant with which to destroy Dracula once and for all!
description.59: Warlock comes face to face with his evil alter ego, the Magus! Is Warlock's fate truly set in stone, or can he avoid his cruel destiny?
description.60: One X-man must make the ultimate sacrifice to save their teammates from certain death. With the team on already shaky ground, how will this loss affect their future?
description.61: Members of the Fantastic Four from alternate universes must band together to foil Arkon's plan. But the fierce Gaard has a few surprises of his own. Will the henchman be a victor for Arkon...or end up in the penalty box?
description.74: The conclusion to John Kowalski's ghostly dance with Death! Will Kowalski find eternal rest at last?
description.75: Morbius encounters another pack of living vampires in the “Bloody Sacrifice!”
description.76: The First Appearance of Ben Reilly, the clone of Spider-Man!  Peter discovers that his biology professor, Dr. Miles Warren, has a few loose screws. As the Jackal, Warren reveals his love for Gwen Stacy and the secret behind her resurrection. Will Spider-Man be able to talk sense into his professor before Jackal takes Ned's life?
description.77: Yellowjacket pushes himself too far fighting off Toad and Whirlwind. Now, Pym can't stop growing! Meanwhile, Scarlet Witch and Vision return from their almost-blissful honeymoon. Wasp awakens from her coma to the relief of her teammates.
description.78: Get ready for an all-action issue! Cap and the Falcon take on S.H.E.I.L.D., Night Shade, and the deadliest robot assassin of all time!
description.79: Meet Marvel's most eclectic super hero team! With the Avengers defending the East Coast, the Champions rise to defend the West. The team assembles for the very first time...amidst a skirmish of the Olympian Gods! Hercules and Venus are being hard-pressed into a plot to overthrow Zeus. Will Black Widow, Ghost Rider, Iceman and Angel, join Hercules in this battle for Olympus?
description.80: A mysterious parasite has found a host -- the love of Mar-Vell's life, UNA!
description.83: Copperhead finds himself with the upper hand over Daredevil but it is unknown who will find themselves six feet under by the end…
description.85: Torkon II, leader of the Toadmen, wants a fantasy world just like the Hulk's! And he'll stop at nothing to achieve Utopia!
description.86: Vengeance in Vietnam! An Avenger exposed! Learn the soul-searing secret hidden in Iron Man's past!
description.87: Can Thor and Jane escape Ulik and the trolls and return to the surface world? Plus, the search for Odin continues!
description.88: The hunt for Dracula continues, as the Lord of the Undead makes his first ever trip to the United States of America!
description.89: With three worlds battling against each other, team members must match up with their Earth-A counterparts to stop the incoming attack from the 5th Dimension! And it's an all-out slugfest!
description.93: Vampire Hunter Blade faces the undead masses in "The Night Josie Harper Died!" With a bounty on his head!
description.94: Read the comic edition of Bram Stoker's Gothic masterpiece...Dracula! Plus, the origin of Manphibian!
description.97: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 12: Killmonger, allied with his assassins, an army, and a few dinosaurs, descends on Central Wakanda to confront Black Panther at Warrior Falls!

3.text: Daimon Hellstrom's home has been defaced by none other than his father Satan, along with his demons!

4.text: The first appearance and origin of Hector Ayala…the notorious White Tiger!

5.text: Here come the Kaptroids...and not even Black Bolt can stop them!

6.text: Luke Cage takes on a mission for the Adonis Chemical Company who have a nasty rat problem on their hands…and we’re not talking rodents.

7.text: Continued from #34, Shang-Chi and Reston race against the clocks to save Leiko from the hourglass!

10.text: Modred must fight off the “Other”, a being of vast power that appears to be channeling the Darkhold!

11.text: There is only so much that Astronaut George Taylor can communicate to ape scientists Zira and Cornelius without the use of his voice. Escape becomes the only option, but can he escape Ape City and live to tell the tale?

12.text: Martial arts masters, Sons of the Tiger, join spider-Man to take out the Crime-Master!

14.text: Martine Bancroft is doomed in the finale to "The End of a Vampire!"

15.text: Daredevil mistakes Torpedo for a villain, and he acts accordingly!

16.text: The saga of Iron Fist begins here! Marvel's mystical Kung Fu crime fighter takes center stage in his own ongoing series. First thing on-tap? Rescuing Detective Colleen Wing! Iron Man guest stars, (and dukes it out with Iron Fist.)

18.text: Captain Marvel is once again combined with Rick Jones! But if Mar-Vell messes up…Rick's life is the one on the line.

19.text: It's an Invaders brawl as its Captain America vs. Sub-Mariner vs. the Human Torch.  Can Captain America rally the team back together?  Plus, the deadly threat of U-Man may destroy the Invaders before they have the chance!

22.text: Tony Stark has the Thing test fly one of his expensive new jets….and the Thing crashes it. But that is not the problem. The bigger problem lies in what the crash landing has now woken up…

23.text: One classic team-up! Spider-Man lends a hand to the FF’s Human Torch when mob bosses capture Johnny Storm.

25.text: While hunkered in a cave, Jonathan stumbles across a group of human survivors who blindly worship a Martian aberration.

26.text: Knowing that Col. Ryker has ties to the mob, Deathlok shoots down a helicopter transporting a mobster who may have pertinent information. Will Deathlok’s trail run dry when the mob man swears to protect Ryker’s whereabouts?

27.text: Martial Arts against Ninja Magic! Shang-Chi stars in “Secrets of the Dragon!”

28.text: Shang-Chi and Clive Reston fly to Mordillo's secluded island in the East China Sea to find Leiko.

29.text: PANTHER’S RAGE CONCLUSION: T’Challa is attacked and held captive by Killmonger’s ‘better’ half, Madam Slay!

30.text: As we learn more of how Belaric Marcosa lived, we also learn about how he died. Will the gang escape from this haunted house before it’s too late?

39.text: Man-on-the-run James Scully, along with a team of scientists, have flown straight into a Bermuda Triangle time-warp! How will Scully and his new comrades navigate a prehistoric world of dinosaurs? A discovery from an ancient alien race unleashes the power of Skull the Slayer. The transformation begins here, but will it also end? The saga of the man trapped 250 million years in the past continues!

43.text: Astronaut George Taylor has been captured by intelligent apes and desperately tries to communicate with them despite his throat injury rendering him mute! Can the lost Astronaut find a way to make the apes understand before it's too late?!

44.text: Torpedo's biggest threat in battle may not be Daredevil, but watching out for that WAL…too late.

45.text: Lee Wing is acting like a man possessed, and Iron Fist grows concerned. What demons are behind this startling transformation? Plus, Danny Rand does battle with Princess Azir’s bodyguard!

47.text: Namor captured by Dr. Dorcas, Attuma, and Tiger Shark! Will Doctor Doom be able to spring the King of Atlantis to uphold his promise to the Atalanteans? Featuring the “spy-fish” of Doom!

48.text: Captain America and the Invaders take on Donar, the God of Storms.  Plus, who is the mysterious Hilda?  And is she friend or foe?

49.text: Baron Mordo faces a threat from inside his own mind. Who, or what, is Nightmare?

52.text: The X-Men’s Beast pulls off a daring rescue, plucking Spider-Man and a scientist from certain death. Afterwards, Spidey and Beast learn about the scientist’s latest project – a savage mutate named the Griffin who’s now seeking revenge against his creator…

53.text: Daimon Hellstrom heads to California to help an old friend with a demon problem, but first he'll have some problems of his own! The cause? None other than his own sister, Satana!

63.text: A team of astronauts crash land on a strange planet and try to find food, water and shelter, but their survival becomes far more dire as they explore the Planet of the Apes!

64.text: What is the "The Key to the Dragon's Heart"?

65.text: Black Bolt and the Inhumans face Blastaar, the living bomb!

66.text: A wrestler doesn't stand a chance against Power Man…until he drinks a magic serum that boosts his strength to superhuman!

67.text: Introducing the world's greatest hunter of monsters -- ULYSSES BLOODSTONE! He has lived and hunted beasts for centuries, but will this be his last hunt?

68.text: Clive Reston sends a car to pick up Shang-Chi and Black Jack Tarr, but they have barely set foot in England when a robot attacks them!

69.text: Jack, along with Lissa, Topaz and Elaine, enter the Marcosa House…which may very well be their final destination given its haunted history!

70.text: Man-Thing writer Steve Gerber explains why he can no longer write about Man-Thing’s adventures! And it all has to do with Dakimh the Mystic!

73.text: Modred, master of the Darkhold? The mystic man from the Dark Ages proclaims to have secret knowledge into the book’s truest evil, recalling an encounter from his days at Camelot.

80.text: A mysterious parasite has found a host -- the love of Mar-Vell's life, UNA!

81.text: It’s a monster mash-up when Man-Wolf joins the fray! The Monster-Maker is intent on creating the most horrific being known to man. Luckily, Spider-Man and Frankenstein’s Monster are on the case! S.H.I.E.L.D. intervenes in a big way. Man-Wolf takes a hit.

83.text: Copperhead finds himself with the upper hand over Daredevil but it is unknown who will find themselves six feet under by the end…

84.text: Attack of the Monstroid! During a softball game, Danny and Rafael Scarfe face an attack by a horrific robot! Who is behind this engineered terror? Colleen Wing proves her mettle while sparring with the Immortal Iron Fist.

92.text: The Thing has plans to take a vacation to Disney World! But will it truly be the Happiest Place on Earth for the ever lovin' Ben Grimm?

95.text: Shang-Chi has a spook-filled smackdown in "Demons in Painted Death"!

96.text: Sir Denis puts Shang-Chi and Black Jack Tarr on a boat to London for their next mission!

97.text: PANTHER’S RAGE PART 12: Killmonger, allied with his assassins, an army, and a few dinosaurs, descends on Central Wakanda to confront Black Panther at Warrior Falls!

98.text: Suspecting they’re all on the same side, the police target Man-Thing and the demons of Thog!
